'''Odaxelagnia''' is a [[paraphilia]] involving sexual arousal through biting, or being bitten. Odaxelagnia is considered a mild form of [[Sadism and masochism|sadism]].<ref>{{citation |title=Vampire Nation |author=Arlene Russo |publisher=Llewellyn Worldwide |year=2008 |isbn=978-0-7387-1456-1 | accessdate = 2011-06-04 | url = https://books.google.com/?id=Bz83hzRnri8C&pg=PT160&dq=Odaxelagnia#v=onepage&q=Odaxelagnia&f=false }}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=The Encyclopedia of Unusual Sex Practices |author=Brenda Love |publisher=Natl Book Network |year=1994 |isbn=978-1-56980-011-9}}</ref><ref>{{Citation |title=Nomenclatura de las manifestaciones sexuales |author=Juan Carlos Romi |date=April 2004 |volume=11 |issue=2 |journal=Alcmeón | accessdate = 2011-06-04 | url = http://alcmeon.com.ar/11/42/01_romi.htm |language=Spanish |location=Revista Argentina de Clínica Neuropsiquiátrica (Argentina Journal of Neuropsychiatric Clinic) }}</ref> [[Alfred Kinsey]] studied Odaxelagnia, reporting that roughly half of all people surveyed had experienced sexual arousal from biting.<ref>{{citation |title=Bite Sighs: A beginner's guide to odaxelagnia |author= Dr. Mark griffiths |url= http://drmarkgriffiths.wordpress.com/2012/12/23/bite-sighs-a-beginners-guide-to-odaxelagnia%E2%80%AC/ | accessdate = 2014-03-19}}</ref> Odaxelagnia has associations with [[vampire lifestyle]]s, but does not necessarily involve bloodletting.<ref>{{Cite web | title = 10 Unusual Fetishes That Some Call Sexy But I Call Yuck &#124; The Stir | accessdate = 2011-06-04 | url = http://thestir.cafemom.com/love_sex/110432/10_unusual_fetishes_that_some }}</ref>
